### What problem does this feature solve?
What benefit does asynchronous server rendering offer? I argue that it's very little if any.

Making the `renderToString` function async guarantees that the oldest requests being processed aren't the highest priority (this is very bad!). It also leads to more memory usage: rendering eight requests asynchronously and simultaneously means that the non-blocking call requires all eight requests' resources be held in memory at once instead of just one at a time (this is also very bad!).

Offering a simpler API would not only be easier for developers, but it would guarantee requests are prioritized in order (don't use resources for the next request until we've finished the last request). It would also decrease memory usage (less overhead overall) and unnecessarily queueing tasks to the event loop (less overhead overall and per request).


### What does the proposed API look like?
```
import { createRenderer } from 'vue-server-renderer';

const renderer = createRenderer({ runInNewContext: false });

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  const markup =  renderer.renderToStringSync(new Component());
  res.end(markup);
});
```

